		<div class="title">Re: FTL</div>
	
	<div class="content">
		<blockquote class="restore">When I first saw this game, it reminded me of playing games in Windows 3.1. I watched the TotalBiscuit thing and decided it didn't look so bad afterall. Knowing that I would not have time to play Guild Wars 2 because of work, I went ahead and picked this up. Very addicting, I was up way too late playing it.<br />
<br />
I thought I was tough stuff on my first run and of course hubris came knocking. I then suffered disaster after disaster four times in a row, before getting my best run all the way to a not so glorious death at the end. Eventually I wasn't able to destroy my adversaries and had to keep jumping out at the last second. Appropriately enough during this sequence the game started a music track that reminded me of Battlestar Gallactica.<br />
<br />
There is a lot of nice variation, although I still hope they make another with more refined features. I also want Evil Genius level/style graphics, but that's a pipe dream. :p<br />
<br />
<div class="bbcode_container">
	<div class="bbcode_description">Quote:</div>
	<div class="bbcode_quote printable">
		<hr />
		
			<div>
				Originally Posted by <strong>Droigan</strong>
				<a href="showthread.php?p=1756750#post1756750" rel="nofollow"><img class="inlineimg" src="images/buttons/viewpost.gif" alt="View Post" /></a>
			</div>
			<div class="message">Looking at the achievements, it might actually be very difficult to achieve 6 different races as crew members. I have only seen human, rock, mantis, engi, z something. Never gotten them in the same playthrough though. Not sure what the 6th race is.</div>
			
		<hr />
	</div>
</div>On my very best playthrough I had a human, rock, and engi, but also had found mysterious stasis pods during an event. Unfortunately I got to the end before I found an event that opens them. I wouldn't be surprised if that gave the last race.<br />
<br />
I got creamed on that run by the way, never even saw the boss. I'm wondering if spending scrap on hull repairs instead of upgrade just delays the inevitable.<br />
<br />
The game has a way of screwing you over without warning, but also coming to the rescue without warning. I had a run where I was constantly out of fuel, sure I would eventually just be stranded, and on the very last jump I found a huge cache of fuel. Of course, a jump later I got destroyed by a battlecruiser that shoots solar flares, but whatever! <br />
<br />
<div class="bbcode_container">
